nails were now long and sharp.

“Not too sharp, are they, my dear,” he asked for the benefit of dura Cordula, who should have gone to the “powder room”—a forlorn hope.

“Why, no,” said Ada.

“You don’t,” he went on, unable to stop, “you don’t scratch little people when you stroke little people? Look at your little girl friend’s hand” (taking it), “look at those dainty short nails (cold innocent, docile little paw!). She could not catch them in the fanciest satin, oh